title: Sunlite 87912 LED T8 is Plug & Play U-Bend Light Tube, 6 in, 11.5W (T8/T12/U6 Fluorescent Replacement) 1800 Lm, 2X Medium Bi-Pin Base (2G13) Dual End Connection, UL Listed, 5000K Daylight, 6 Count
features: UPGRADE TO LED - Replace your inefficient T8 fluorescent U bulbs with energy saving LED bulbs from Sunlite. They are instant on at full brightness with no buzzing or flickering. Our shatterproof Glass tubes help prevent yellowing and bending over time. High Color Rendering Index (CRI) rating of 82

PLUG AND PLAY - These bulbs are direct replacements for 32W/23T8/U6 Tubes with no bypass required. Features a 2X medium Bi-Pin base. They are electronic ballast compatible. A complete list of compatible ballasts is located directly under the product information in a pdf for your reference

ENERGY EFFICIENT - Each bulb puts out a bright 1800 lumens of light with a 5000K Super White color temperature while only using 11.5 watts of electricity! Annual energy costs are a low $1.38 (Based on 3 hours/day at $0.11/kWh)
LONG LIFE - With a life span of up to 50,000 hours you'll be required to replace difficult to access bulbs less often. You will save maintenance costs and save energy at the same time

UL LISTED - These shatterproof led bulbs are UL Listed and have been tested to meet their rigorous safety standards. Unlike fluorescent tubes, led tubes contain no harmful chemicals and do not require special handling or disposal
description: Upgrade your T8 fluorescent U-Bend tubes with energy efficient LED plug and play tubes, a direct replacement with no ballast bypass required. They are instant on at full brightness with no buzzing or flickering. With a life span of up to 50,000 hours you will be required to replace difficult to reach bulbs less often. You'll save maintenance costs and save energy at the same time. Can be used for both commercial and residential locations. They are UL Listed and have been tested to meet their rigorous safety standards. Unlike fluorescent tubes, led tubes contain no harmful chemicals and do not require special handling or disposal.
